Description: Replace RainbowKit with Reown AppKit for wallet connections

Installation:
```sh
npm install @web3modal/wagmi @web3modal/wagmi-react
```

Setup (src/pages/_app.tsx):
```tsx
import { createWeb3Modal, defaultWagmiConfig } from '@web3modal/wagmi/react';
import { base } from 'wagmi/chains';

const projectId = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_PROJECT_ID;
const chains = [base];

const wagmiConfig = defaultWagmiConfig({ projectId, chains, appName: 'Rift' });

if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
  createWeb3Modal({ projectId, wagmiConfig });
}

// App provider wrap:
<WagmiConfig config={wagmiConfig}>
  <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
    <ChakraProvider theme={theme}>
      <Component {...pageProps} />
    </ChakraProvider>
  </QueryClientProvider>
</WagmiConfig>
```

Usage (`<w3m-button>` component):
- Replace RainbowKit ConnectButton with `<w3m-button></w3m-button>`
- Add TS declaration if needed.

Handle previous `openConnectModal()`:
- Prefer user interaction with `<w3m-button>`
- Programmatic open via Web3Modal.open() if absolutely necessary.
